headline: Week’s Best: Trump’s Tax Bill Passes House
summary: The Republican tax and spending bill narrowly passed the House of Representatives early Thursday and now heads to the Senate.  Recent changes to clear the House include moving up the start date of Medicaid work requirements to December 2026 instead of 2029 and accelerating the end of some tax credits for wind and solar energy.  The changes also included increasing the cap on the state and local tax deduction to $40,000 from $30,000 in the previous plan.
